text: Facing a summer with no baseball and no picnics, the makers of the original Coney Island red hot feared the worst. But even with an empty boardwalk, business is booming. https://t.co/blERtt9pGV

text: “People are dying in hospitals and dying at home. The official tolls are almost certainly an undercount. The morgues are overflowing. Those are the facts. But where is the grief?” Teju Cole writes for @NYTmag https://t.co/XoFVX3E5hO
